## File Map

| File | Action | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| `convex/sendApi.ts` | Modify | Replace `callUnipileSend` with Gmail API send |
| `convex/dispatcher.ts` | Modify | Replace `sendViaUnipile` with Gmail API send |
| `convex/slack.ts` | Modify | Remove Unipile fallback from `sendApprovedReply` |
| `convex/connect.ts` | Modify | Replace Unipile-based Gmail connect/status/disconnect with gmailCredentials |
| `convex/send.ts` | Modify | Remove `callUnipileSend`, keep only `recordSendSuccess`/`recordSendFailure`/`recordAuthFailure` mutations |
| `convex/gmailApi.ts` | Modify | Add `sendViaGmailApi` internalAction (wraps auth resolve + callGmailSend) |

---

### Task 1: Add `sendViaGmailApi` internalAction to `gmailApi.ts`

**Files:**
- Modify: `convex/gmailApi.ts`

The building blocks exist (`getAccessTokenForUser`, `callGmailSend`). We need one action that the dispatcher and sendApi can call.

- [ ] **Step 1: Add `sendViaGmailApi` action**

Add this after the existing `callGmailSend` function (around line 458) in `convex/gmailApi.ts`:

```typescript
// Send email via Gmail API — used by dispatcher and sendApi
export const sendViaGmailApi = internalAction({
  args: {
    userId: v.string(),
    taskId: v.string(),
    to: v.string(),
    subject: v.string(),
    body: v.string(),
    threadId: v.optional(v.string()),
    inReplyTo: v.optional(v.string()),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const gmailAuth = await getAccessTokenForUser(ctx, args.userId);
    if (!gmailAuth) {
      await ctx.runMutation(internal.send.recordAuthFailure, {
        userId: args.userId,
        taskId: args.taskId,
        mailboxId: "",
        error: "Gmail credentials expired or not found",
      });
      return { ok: false, error: "Gmail credentials expired" };
    }

    const result = await callGmailSend({
      accessToken: gmailAuth.accessToken,
      from: gmailAuth.email,
      to: args.to,
      subject: args.subject,
      body: args.body,
      threadId: args.threadId,
      inReplyTo: args.inReplyTo,
    });

    if (!result.ok) {
      if (result.authError) {
        await ctx.runMutation(internal.send.recordAuthFailure, {
          userId: args.userId,
          taskId: args.taskId,
          mailboxId: "",
          error: result.error,
        });
      } else {
        await ctx.runMutation(internal.send.recordSendFailure, {
          userId: args.userId,
          taskId: args.taskId,
          error: result.error,
        });
      }
      return { ok: false, error: result.error };
    }

    await ctx.runMutation(internal.send.recordSendSuccess, {
      userId: args.userId,
      taskId: args.taskId,
      unipileMessageId: result.messageId,
      providerId: result.threadId,
    });

    return { ok: true, messageId: result.messageId, threadId: result.threadId };
  },
});
```

